OL,3,CWelfare on the line as government
OL,4,Clooks for possible savings
OL,6,FA number of senior sources across
OL,7,Fgovernment have told me that they have
OL,8,Fbeen asked to identify the 20% of
OL,9,Fspending within their departments that
OL,10,Fthey see as lowest priority.
OL,12,FOne suggested that they had been asked
OL,13,Fto go even further - up to 40%.
OL,15,FThe move - which I revealed on the
OL,16,FTalking Politics podcast - underlines
OL,17,Fa series of likely difficult decisions
OL,18,Facross government spending - alongside
OL,19,Fbillions in welfare cuts - in this
OL,20,Fspring's spending review.
